title: Russia launches dozens of drone strikes on Ukraine overnight
description: Russia launched dozens of drone strikes across Ukraine on the eve of a holiday celebrating the defeat of Nazi Germany.

title: Woman stranded in Australian bush for five days survives by drinking wine
description: A woman who was stranded in the Australian bush for five days survived by eating sweets and drinking a bottle of wine.

title: Mystery Chinese spacecraft returns to Earth after 276 days in orbit
description: An experimental Chinese spacecraft has returned to Earth after staying in orbit for 276 days, China's state media has reported.

title: Iran hangs two men for blasphemy as rise in executions continues
description: Iran has executed two men accused of blasphemy, as a rise in death sentences handed out by the ruling regime continues.

title: More than 400 killed in 'worst flood we have ever had' in DR Congo
description: More than 400 people have been killed in flash floods in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo - making it one of the deadliest natural disasters in the country's recent history.

title: 'Spelling mistake' noticed in coronation invite to Ukraine's first lady
description: The coronation invite to the Ukrainian first lady has caused a stir on social media  due to a potential "spelling mistake".

title: Bolivian general who captured Che Guevara dies
description: Ernesto "Che" Guevara's captor, a former Bolivian general, has died at the age of 84.

title: At least 21 drown after boat capsizes in India
description: A boat has capsized in southern India, killing at least 21 people, authorities have said.
